First, we need to convert the given base-13 numbers to base-10 numbers.

Starting with \( B651_{13} \):
- B in base-13 is 11 in base-10.
- 6 in base-13 is 6 in base-10.
- 5 in base-13 is 5 in base-10.
- 1 in base-13 is 1 in base-10.

The value of \( B651_{13} \) can be converted to base-10 as follows:
\[
B651_{13} = 11 \cdot 13^3 + 6 \cdot 13^2 + 5 \cdot 13^1 + 1 \cdot 13^0
\]
\[
= 11 \cdot 2197 + 6 \cdot 169 + 5 \cdot 13 + 1 \cdot 1
\]
\[
= 11 \cdot 2197 = 24167
\]
\[
= 6 \cdot 169 = 1014
\]
\[
= 5 \cdot 13 = 65
\]
\[
= 1 \cdot 1 = 1
\]
\[
B651_{13} = 24167 + 1014 + 65 + 1 = 25247_{10}
\]

Next, convert \( C712_{13} \):
- C in base-13 is 12 in base-10.
- 7 in base-13 is 7 in base-10.
- 1 in base-13 is 1 in base-10.
- 2 in base-13 is 2 in base-10.

The value of \( C712_{13} \) can be converted to base-10 as follows:
\[
C712_{13} = 12 \cdot 13^3 + 7 \cdot 13^2 + 1 \cdot 13^1 + 2 \cdot 13^0
\]
\[
= 12 \cdot 2197 + 7 \cdot 169 + 1 \cdot 13 + 2 \cdot 1
\]
\[
= 12 \cdot 2197 = 26364
\]
\[
= 7 \cdot 169 = 1183
\]
\[
= 1 \cdot 13 = 13
\]
\[
= 2 \cdot 1 = 2
\]
\[
C712_{13} = 26364 + 1183 + 13 + 2 = 27562_{10}
\]

Now add the two base-10 equivalents:
\[
25247 + 27562 = 52809_{10}
\]

Finally, convert \( 52809_{10} \) back to base-13. To do this, we need to divide by successive powers of 13 and keep track of the remainders.

First, find the highest power of 13 that fits into 52809:
\[
13^4 = 28561 \quad (fits into 52809)
\]
\[
13^5 = 371293 \quad (too large)
\]

Now perform the division:
\[
52809 \div 28561 = 1 \quad \text{remainder } 24248
\]

Next:
\[
24248 \div 2197 = 11 \quad \text{remainder } 61  \quad \text{(B in base-13)}
\]

Next:
\[
61 \div 169 = 0 \quad \text{remainder } 61
\]

Next:
\[
61 \div 13 = 4 \quad \text{remainder } 9
\]

Next:
\[
9 \div 1 = 9 \quad \text{remainder } 9
\]

So, \( 52809_{10} = 1B049_{13} \).

Summarizing:
\[
B651_{13} + C712_{13} = 25247_{10} + 27562_{10} = 52809_{10} = 1B049_{13}
\]